
[1]commemorate

   COMMEMORATE, v.t. To call to remembrance by a solemn act; to celebrate
   with honor and solemnity; to honor, as a person or event, by some act
   of respect or affection, intended to preserve the remembrance of that
   person or event.

   The Lords supper is designed to commemorate the sufferings and dying
   love of our Savior.
